title: Jackie And Roy - Lovesick (1966) Verve 24/96 vinyl
description:
LOVESICK

A swinging dissertation on the state of bliss
as diagnosed by the incurably romantic

JACKIE AND ROY

24/96 STEREO vinyl rip (like all my rips, pure and unfiltered)

SIDE A:
Lovesick
Samba Triste (Sad Samba)
Mimosa And Me
Corcovado (Quiet Nights Of Stars)
Such A Lonely Girl Am I
A Big Beautiful Ball

SIDE B:
Let's Begin
I Wonder What's The Matter With Me
If You Could See Me Now
Mountain Greenery
You Really Started Something
The World Is Your Ballon

Jackie Cain - vocals
Roy Kral - piano & vocals
Don Payne - electric bass
Don MacDonald - drums

Recorded at Van Gelder Studios, Englewood Cliffs, NJ on December 9 & 20, 1966

Verve V-8688
